        "created_at": "2025-07-18T02:09:02.494Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The topic states it all.</p>\n<p>Right now, the <strong>red squiggly underline used for spellcheck is nearly impossible to see</strong> against a dark background, and there are no options in settings to customize it — only the broad choices: <em>Use System Theme</em>, <em>Dark Mode</em>, and <em>Light Mode</em>.</p>\n<p>My goal is either to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Change the color of the spellcheck underline (ideally to cyan or another visible tone), or</li>\n<li>Fully theme the app using a consistent dark color scheme like Solarized Dark.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I’ve already attempted CSS injection by unpacking and editing <code>app.asar</code>, injecting styles via JavaScript (into <code>preload.bundle.js</code>), and repacking. While CSS injection technically worked (confirmed via test styles), it <strong>did not affect the spellcheck underline</strong>, and UI theming results were limited.</p>\n<p>So the question is:</p>\n<pre><code>Is it even possible to change the color of the spellcheck underline in Signal Desktop?\n\nIs there any known method to fully theme the Signal Desktop interface beyond the built-in options?\n</code></pre>\n<p>Thanks</p>",
