        "created_at": "2025-07-22T13:37:32.568Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Signal desktop is an electron app. So it’s text boxes are chromium text boxes with the associated spell check code.</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::spelling-error\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/e/7e875ebfad1ef423b92d8a16a46961350a77483c.png\" class=\"site-icon\" data-dominant-color=\"3F3E43\" width=\"48\" height=\"48\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::spelling-error\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">MDN Web Docs</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/387;\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/f/4/f43c65b3b818a2ea578c6a20ce48f67e84ba4d29_2_690x388.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" data-dominant-color=\"060909\" width=\"690\" height=\"388\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::spelling-error\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">::spelling-error - CSS | MDN</a></h3>\n\n  <p>The ::spelling-error CSS pseudo-element represents a text segment which the user agent has flagged as incorrectly spelled.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>should allow you to stylize the spell check error coloring.</p>",
